snippet: President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi has made the project the cornerstone of his plans to revive the economy, but the benefits pledged have not eased investors’ doubts.
abstract: Egyptian Pres Abdel Fattah el-Sisi inaugurates new addition to Suez Canal as state media organizations celebrate opening of section; Sisi calls addition 'new Suez Canal,' but it is in fact parallel side channel that may not live up to president's promises that country will reap numerous economic rewards from expansion.
lead_paragraph: President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi has made the project the cornerstone of his plans to revive the economy, but the benefits pledged have not eased investors’ doubts.

headline.main: Suez Canal Upgrade May Not Ease Egypt’s Economic Journey
headline.print_headline: Suez Upgrade May Not Ease Egypt’s Economic Journey
